Live the Hype in Hurghada

The transformation of Hurghada from quiet fishing village to the premier tourist destination in Egypt is complete. If you are looking for a beachside holiday in a first-class hotel or resort, then Hurghada has some of the best in Egypt, along with a lively nightlife scene and diverse shopping.

Bargain for a souvenir in old town El Dahar with its more traditional bazaars, and the city centre of Sekalla has many top class hotels. Marine Boulevard is lined with restaurants and designer stores.

The popularity of outranking the Giza Pyramids, Valley of the Kings and Abu Simbel has impacted some of those precious coral reefs along the Red Sea Riviera coast. However, there are still great diving spots to be found. Try the nearby coast around the tourist resort town of El Gouna or the uninhabited Giftun Island is ideal for snorkelling with its coral gardens. The eastern portion of the Sahara Desert with its Red Sea Mountains and nomadic Bedouin tribes can be explored from Hurghada on camels.

Whether you are looking for an all-inclusive family resort on Hurghada beach, a self-catering apartment with private pool or a touch of luxury in Soma Bay, Booking.com has your choice covered. Hurghada International Airport has direct flights from many European locations.
